The paper presents a distributed algorithm for maximum flow in undirected weighted networks, which involves communication between nodes. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The algorithm also involves constructing a spanning tree and a cut approximator, which suggests that it may also belong to the Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of randomization, which is a common technique in the Approximation Algorithms (cs.DM) and Algorithms (cs.AL) sub-categories.
